<quantity id="236CB5EF514A1827FD93FB18ED7518E5" box="[522,589,1159,1186]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="113" pageNumber="114" unit="mm" value="6.0">6 mm</quantity>
long) with orange pronotum and very dark brown elytra which are orange margined narrowly along the lateral margins; most obviously distinguished by the anterior emargination of the entire LO in 
<date id="902A3ECA514A1827FEB5FB4FEE7618AD" box="[300,334,1232,1258]" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">V7</date>
and the posterior outlines of both 
<date id="902A3ECA514A1827FD42FB4FEDC518AD" box="[731,765,1232,1258]" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">V7</date>
and T8; the MPP is wide and apically acute bearing small dorsally curving hooks along its lateral margins (these hooks are not obviously visible from below); T8 is strongly produced posteriorly into two acute prolongations which border the strong median emargination. Elytral apices ae not deflexed and a MFC does not appear to be present (see below).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="AC8E4B81514A1825FF5EFAC0EC401C90" lastPageId="115" lastPageNumber="116" pageId="113" pageNumber="114" type="description">
<paragraph id="E42B180A514A1825FF5EFAC0EC401C90" blockId="113.[151,1437,1051,2014]" lastBlockId="115.[151,1437,152,611]" lastPageId="115" lastPageNumber="116" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">
<emphasis id="D6E0C418514A1827FF5EFAC0EEF4193D" bold="true" box="[199,460,1375,1402]" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">Redescription of male</emphasis>
. 5.7–6.1 mm long. Colour (
<figureCitation id="7CAF048F514A1827FC9BFAC0EC98193D" box="[770,928,1375,1402]" captionStart="FIGURES 345−355" captionStartId="114.[151,264,1894,1919]" captionTargetBox="[213,1370,166,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@114.[213,1375,166,1875]" captionTargetPageId="114" captionText="FIGURES 345−355. Medeopteryx timida comb. nov. Saigon male (MNHN). 345 habitus dorsal; 346 habitus ventral; 347, 348 terminal abdomen: 347 ventral; 348 dorsal; 349, 350 dissected terminal abdomen after soaking in soapy water for an hour: 349 ventral (base of lateral hooks on ML arrowed); 350 left lateral (hooks arising from ML arrowed); 351−353 aedeagal sheath: 351 left lateral; 352 ventral; 353 dorsal; 354, 355 aedeagus: 354 ventral; 355 right lateral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508236" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508236/files/figure.png" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">Figs 345, 346</figureCitation>
): pronotum bright orange; MS and MN dingy orange yellow; elytra very dark brown with lateral margin narrowly orange in anterior half; head between eyes black; antennae incomplete, segments dark brown; venter of pro and mesothorax orange, of metathorax dark brown; legs brown with darker brown tibiae and tarsi; basal abdominal ventrites brown; posterior margin of 
<date id="902A3ECA514A1827FA94FA54EA1719A1" box="[1293,1327,1483,1510]" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">V5</date>
narrowly and irregularly white; LO in 
<date id="902A3ECA514A1827FE44FA70ED3A1A4E" box="[477,514,1519,1545]" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">V6</date>
, 7 appearing orange yellow; abdominal tergites pale mottled brown semitransparent with underlying fat body visible beneath cuticle; T8 semitransparent with two lateral lines of fat body visible beneath cuticle. Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="7CAF048F514A1827FE51F9A8ED121A15" box="[456,554,1591,1618]" captionStart="FIGURES 345−355" captionStartId="114.[151,264,1894,1919]" captionTargetBox="[213,1370,166,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@114.[213,1375,166,1875]" captionTargetPageId="114" captionText="FIGURES 345−355. Medeopteryx timida comb. nov. Saigon male (MNHN). 345 habitus dorsal; 346 habitus ventral; 347, 348 terminal abdomen: 347 ventral; 348 dorsal; 349, 350 dissected terminal abdomen after soaking in soapy water for an hour: 349 ventral (base of lateral hooks on ML arrowed); 350 left lateral (hooks arising from ML arrowed); 351−353 aedeagal sheath: 351 left lateral; 352 ventral; 353 dorsal; 354, 355 aedeagus: 354 ventral; 355 right lateral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508236" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508236/files/figure.png" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">Fig. 345</figureCitation>
): lateral margins convex sided (B&gt; A or C); width less than humeral width. Elytron: subparallel sided; apices not deflexed; no interstitial lines. Head: GHW 
<date id="902A3ECA514A1827FC6CF9C4EB261A31" box="[1013,1054,1627,1654]" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">6 X</date>
SIW; ASD subequal to or slightly&gt; ASW. Mouthparts: apical labial palpomere laterally flattened inner edge entire.Antennae: incomplete; FS filiform subequal in length to half FS1; FS1 subequal in length to scape. Legs: no MFC (see below); no segments expanded or excavated. Abdomen (
<figureCitation id="7CAF048F514A1827FE2FF958ED621AA5" box="[438,602,1735,1762]" captionStart="FIGURES 345−355" captionStartId="114.[151,264,1894,1919]" captionTargetBox="[213,1370,166,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@114.[213,1375,166,1875]" captionTargetPageId="114" captionText="FIGURES 345−355. Medeopteryx timida comb. nov. Saigon male (MNHN). 345 habitus dorsal; 346 habitus ventral; 347, 348 terminal abdomen: 347 ventral; 348 dorsal; 349, 350 dissected terminal abdomen after soaking in soapy water for an hour: 349 ventral (base of lateral hooks on ML arrowed); 350 left lateral (hooks arising from ML arrowed); 351−353 aedeagal sheath: 351 left lateral; 352 ventral; 353 dorsal; 354, 355 aedeagus: 354 ventral; 355 right lateral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508236" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508236/files/figure.png" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">Figs 346−350</figureCitation>
): ventrites anterior to the LO not obviously emarginated across posterior margins; LO in 
<date id="902A3ECA514A1827FED7F974EE481B42" box="[334,368,1771,1797]" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">V6</date>
entire; LO in 
<date id="902A3ECA514A1827FD8FF973ED001B41" box="[534,568,1772,1798]" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">V7</date>
entire, with small triangular median anterior emargination and extending to lateral margins and into MPP; PLP short rounded; MPP elongate extending well beyond PLP apices, and apically acute, bearing short slender dorsally curving projections along its lateral margins (basal areas of these projections not visible in dried specimen, visible after specimen was soaked in soapy water; see 
<figureCitation id="7CAF048F514A1827FB83F8C8EB8F1B35" box="[1050,1207,1879,1906]" captionStart="FIGURES 345−355" captionStartId="114.[151,264,1894,1919]" captionTargetBox="[213,1370,166,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@114.[213,1375,166,1875]" captionTargetPageId="114" captionText="FIGURES 345−355. Medeopteryx timida comb. nov. Saigon male (MNHN). 345 habitus dorsal; 346 habitus ventral; 347, 348 terminal abdomen: 347 ventral; 348 dorsal; 349, 350 dissected terminal abdomen after soaking in soapy water for an hour: 349 ventral (base of lateral hooks on ML arrowed); 350 left lateral (hooks arising from ML arrowed); 351−353 aedeagal sheath: 351 left lateral; 352 ventral; 353 dorsal; 354, 355 aedeagus: 354 ventral; 355 right lateral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508236" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508236/files/figure.png" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">Figs 349, 350</figureCitation>
). T8: ventral surface with well-defined lateral ridges and apically rounded flanges which incline anteriorly with their apices curving upwards; anterolateral paired prolongations of tergite as long as posterior entire portion, expanded in horizontal plane and apically rounded; T7 with apically acute projecting posterolateral corners. Aedeagal sheath (
<figureCitation id="7CAF048F514A1827FB6AF85CEAAC1B99" box="[1267,1428,1987,2014]" captionStart="FIGURES 345−355" captionStartId="114.[151,264,1894,1919]" captionTargetBox="[213,1370,166,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@114.[213,1375,166,1875]" captionTargetPageId="114" captionText="FIGURES 345−355. Medeopteryx timida comb. nov. Saigon male (MNHN). 345 habitus dorsal; 346 habitus ventral; 347, 348 terminal abdomen: 347 ventral; 348 dorsal; 349, 350 dissected terminal abdomen after soaking in soapy water for an hour: 349 ventral (base of lateral hooks on ML arrowed); 350 left lateral (hooks arising from ML arrowed); 351−353 aedeagal sheath: 351 left lateral; 352 ventral; 353 dorsal; 354, 355 aedeagus: 354 ventral; 355 right lateral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508236" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508236/files/figure.png" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">Figs 351−353</figureCitation>
) of the form of New Guinean 
<taxonomicName id="2394638951481825FE44FF06ED571CF4" authorityName="Ballantyne in Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" authorityYear="2013" box="[477,623,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Medeopteryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="115" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D6E0C41851481825FE44FF06ED571CF4" box="[477,623,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">Medeopteryx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, without well-defined paraprocts. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="7CAF048F51481825FBF4FF06EA351CF4" box="[1133,1293,152,179]" captionStart="FIGURES 345−355" captionStartId="114.[151,264,1894,1919]" captionTargetBox="[213,1370,166,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@114.[213,1375,166,1875]" captionTargetPageId="114" captionText="FIGURES 345−355. Medeopteryx timida comb. nov. Saigon male (MNHN). 345 habitus dorsal; 346 habitus ventral; 347, 348 terminal abdomen: 347 ventral; 348 dorsal; 349, 350 dissected terminal abdomen after soaking in soapy water for an hour: 349 ventral (base of lateral hooks on ML arrowed); 350 left lateral (hooks arising from ML arrowed); 351−353 aedeagal sheath: 351 left lateral; 352 ventral; 353 dorsal; 354, 355 aedeagus: 354 ventral; 355 right lateral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508236" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508236/files/figure.png" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">Figs 354, 355</figureCitation>
): b/a 0.5; LL very short separated along their dorsal surface by 2/3 their length.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="B0EB488251491824FF0EF8F9ECCE1BAC" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508236" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3508236" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508236/files/figure.png" pageId="114" pageNumber="115" startId="114.[151,264,1894,1919]" targetBox="[213,1370,166,1875]" targetPageId="114">
