<subSubSection id="AC8E4B8151481825FF5EFF7EEAA11E24" pageId="115" pageNumber="116" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="E42B180A51481825FF5EFF7EEC7E1D67" blockId="115.[151,1437,152,611]" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">
<emphasis id="D6E0C41851481825FF5EFF7EEE031CBC" bold="true" box="[199,315,225,251]" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="800565FB51481825FEDBFF7EED3E1CBC" author="Bourgeois" box="[322,518,225,251]" firstAuthor="Bourgeois" pageId="115" pageNumber="116" pagination="161 - 171" refId="ref115480" refString="Bourgeois, J. (1890) Contributions a la faune Indo-Chinoise. Rhipidoceridae, Dascillidae, Malacodermidae. Annales de la Societe entomologique de France, 6 (10), 161 - 171." type="journal article" year="1890">Bourgeois (1890)</bibRefCitation>
indicated he saw 
<specimenCount id="F292D38351481825FD56FF7EEC611CBC" box="[719,857,225,251]" pageId="115" pageNumber="116" type="generic">8 specimens</specimenCount>
determined by Olivier and concluded that Olivier’s original specimen must have been a female (confirmed here).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E42B180A51481825FF5EFEB6EBE91E5C" blockId="115.[151,1437,152,611]" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">
We do not believe 
<taxonomicName id="2394638951481825FE01FEB6ED181D04" authorityName="Ho" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Olivier" baseAuthorityYear="1883" box="[408,544,297,323]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Medeopteryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="115" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="timida">
<emphasis id="D6E0C41851481825FE01FEB6EEF21D04" box="[408,458,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">Med</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="D6E0C41851481825FE41FEB6ED181D04" box="[472,544,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">timida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been recorded from New 
<collectingCountry id="9C83589A51481825FCE9FEB6ECFC1D04" box="[880,964,297,323]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">Guinea</collectingCountry>
, and no observations of collections of that fauna have revealed any males. 
<bibRefCitation id="800565FB51481825FE65FED2ED911D20" author="Olivier" box="[508,681,333,359]" firstAuthor="Olivier" pageId="115" pageNumber="116" pagination="417 - 422" refId="ref120984" refString="Olivier, E. (1913 a) Lampyridae. Resultats de L'Expedition Scientifique Neerlandaise a la Nouvelle-Guinee en 1907 et 1909 sous les auspices de Dr H. R. Lorentz. Zoologie Livraison III. Nova Guinea, 9, 417 - 422." type="journal article" year="1913" yearSuffix="a">Olivier (1913a)</bibRefCitation>
listed several New Guinean records for this species from islands of Kiriwina, Fergusson and Trobriand. LB examined 
<specimenCount id="F292D38351481825FD4DFEEEEC791DCC" box="[724,833,369,395]" pageId="115" pageNumber="116" type="female">3 females</specimenCount>
in his collection (in MNHN) which he had placed to one side alongside males which were labelled as 
<taxonomicName id="2394638951481825FD20FE09EC261DE8" authorityName="Ho" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Olivier" baseAuthorityYear="1883" box="[697,798,405,431]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Medeopteryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="115" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="timida">
<emphasis id="D6E0C41851481825FD20FE09EC261DE8" box="[697,798,405,431]" italics="true" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">L. timida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In the absence of reliably associated males it is impossible to assign these females and LB observed three slightly different patterns to the outlines of the terminal ventrites, and concluded that the two females from Fergusson Is were not conspecific but we were unable to determine their correct identity. 
<bibRefCitation id="800565FB51481825FED7FD9EED601E5B" author="Ballantyne" box="[334,600,513,540]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Ballantyne" pageId="115" pageNumber="116" pagination="1 - 7" refId="ref114336" refString="Ballantyne, L. A &amp; Jusoh, W. F. A. (2016) List of genera and species in the Luciolinae from SE Asia and the Australopacific Version 2. Checklist of IndoPacific Luciolinae, 2016, 1 - 7. https: // doi. org / 10.13140 / RG. 2.1.4635.2241" type="journal article" year="2016">
Ballantyne 
<emphasis id="D6E0C41851481825FE57FD9DEEC71E5C" box="[462,511,513,539]" italics="true" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">et al</emphasis>
. (2016)
</bibRefCitation>
figured certain aspects of this species as 
<taxonomicName id="2394638951481825FBBCFD9EEBF21E5C" box="[1061,1226,513,539]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="115" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="timida">
<emphasis id="D6E0C41851481825FBBCFD9EEBF21E5C" box="[1061,1226,513,539]" italics="true" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">Luciola timida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E42B180A51481825FF5EFDBAEAA11E24" blockId="115.[151,1437,152,611]" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">Because we do not yet know the function of the MFC we are unable to assess just what degree of aggregation of hairs at the end of the femur could constitute a MFC and have indicated we believe it is absent in these specimens.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
